g.text: Age: Henry is 59 and Karen is 58
Relationships: Henry and his wife Karen are retired
Location: Live in a congested central neighbourhood
Henry and his wife are retired and want to move out of the inner city to a quieter community. In order to sell their
house, they need to cut down a dying tree in their front yard that is hindering the sale of their house. They decide
to visit calgary.ca to see if they can get details about their property. They ﬁnd a link that takes them to the map
and gives them their property easement and assessment. They realize the tree is on city property and can now
rest assured that the City will take care of the tree for them free of charge. At the same time they click on the
assessment link and ﬁnd out what their house is worth.
It is mid-day and Henry and his wife are at home.
Henry is using his desktop computer.
Henry and Karen would like to do the following: ﬁnd out what their property dimensions are, see how much of
their lot is designated for city use (lot easement), ﬁnd out what their last property assessment was.
